<br>
When playing my paladin, and the ranger in my group pulls, I use a quick Cease to pull aggro onto me, and turn the mob in my direction.  It stops walking for a full second.  Desist is just over a second, maybe two?  It also does not attack.<br>
<br>
As an example... When the paladin was level 25ish, we were grouped in Warsliks Woods at the Giant fort.  The ranger would pull two up to the south-eastern corner hill.  I'd root one at the max root range, and hit the second with Cease.  I'd almost instantly be getting beat on.  <br>
<br>
Similarly, I've been doing this the last couple nights in Eastern Wastes doing Ulthorks and Rhinos.  Ranger pulls past the rogue, I Cease/Desist/Stun, one two three, and the rogue gets off some crit throws while I get in front of the mob and start meleeing.  During this time, the only damage I take is from a riposte.  So for a full 4 seconds or so, I take no damage, and the mob goes down ten percent or more.  (Well except for Rhinos.)<br>
<br>
If you need to, test it yourself... Go up to an orc pawn or whatever, and pull it with a bow or a higher casting stun (nondamage).  As it runs to you, hit it with Cease.  Bam, it stops for a second, then heads after you.<br>
<br>
I also use it for ghetto crowd control.  I Cease/Desist/Stun adds, and either I, the cleric, or the ranger will root it.  Move over a bit, cleric Atones, bam.  Ghetto mez.<br>
